***Velocity Works is proud to now offer HOT BLUING service! If you are interested in having your firearms professionally HOT BLUED right here in central Ohio, call or email us to set it up!***

Velocity Works is proud to offer the custom-built VW Sniper Mosin Nagant. 

The objective of this custom-built rifle was to produce a capable and attractive heavy caliber, long-range precision target rifle that fires inexpensive ammo and can be had for hundreds less than an off-the-shelf item in the same category. 

We started with a conventional 91-30 Hex-receiver (slightly stronger than round-receiver models) Mosin Nagant.  We then removed the action and barrel from the wood stock, and completely degreased, cleaned, inspected, and function checked the firearm.  All the steel was then professionally hot blued on site to bring out the luster of the steel and protect from corrosion.  

For mounting optics, we went with a top-of-the-line picatinny scope mount.  These heavy duty mounts are precision machined out of 6061 aluminum here in the USA.  The mount utilizes 3 mounting points and has a hard coating to resist chips, scratches and corrosion.  These mounts have been tested up to 800 yards with sub-MOA results, quite impressive considering the kick of a 7.62x54R round.  We had the mount professionally installed by our on-sight gunsmith, who measures, fits the parts, and drills and taps the necessary holes to secure the mount. Included with the mount is a custom down-turned bolt handle which allows the clearance to move freely under the scope.  The bolt handle and body were polished to a high-shine finish. 

For optics we mounted a Sniper Precision Optics 4-16x50mm scope.  Features include a red or green illuminated reticle, locking windage and elevation adjustments, and a removable sun shade. 

The action was then fit and installed into a Pro Mag Archangel Mosin Nagant stock.  This new-age, ergonomically friendly, composite stock features a fully adjustable length-of-pull and cheek rest, a small storage compartment, and accepts the included 5-round detachable magazine (10-round mags are available as well).  A Caldwell tilting bipod rounds out the whole package. 

Each of these rifles is fully tested and absolutely ready to fire and enjoy.  If you are looking for a time-tested, heavy caliber, attractive, long range precision target rifle that fires cheap and readily available ammunition while costing hundreds less than the alternatives, purchase one now, or contact us about building one of these custom rifles for you!

title: For Sale:  Romanian -- Dragunov FPK Sniper Rifle w/ scope PSL Romak-3 – Excellent Condition
postcontent: Dragunov-FPK sniper rifle, complete with original military scope(not the imported version) and all of the accessories. These rifles, also known as a Romak-3, SSG-97, and PSL, are extremely accurate and reliable. The Dragunov design has been in use since the mid 60's, and is still the official design of Russia and other Com-bloc countries. This is the Romanian version, which improved on the Russian design as far as reliability goes. This is a great weapon for several reasons. First, it uses the same type of action that an AK-47 uses, which makes it drag-through-the-mud reliable. Second, it's semi-automatic, which means if you miss with the first shot, you have an immediate chance to make up for it. Third, it uses a very powerful 7.62x54R caliber bullet, which is a monster round. The large size of the round and the long barrel of the rifle combine to allow shooting out to 1000yds. A communist sniper issued a Dragunov rifle in the Afghan war stated that he felt confident hitting people out to 800 yds with one shot, and vehicles up to 1000 yds. These features make the perfect long-range weapon for any situation. This rifle comes complete with scope(very cool, built in range-finder reticle which was originally lit with radioactive Tritium), Comes with a hardcase. Quantities of these rifles are extremely limited. That is why these are very scarce and will only become more so.

title: For Sale:  Rock River LAR PDS piston with Quad Rail Handguard
postcontent:
I'm selling my rock river LAR-PDS piston operated AR.  This gun is VERY hard to find, especially the rifle version.  The short stroke piston operating system works flawlessly.  This is a fantastic gun and is in excellent condition.  I've put at most 200-300 rounds through it.  I've not had a single failure of any kind with it, and it is very accurate.  It will shoot sub 1.5" groups at 100 yards with cheap bulk ammo.  And that's with the 4x optic shown on it.  With higher quality ammo I'm sure it will shoot sub MOA.  I really like this gun, but I just have too many guns and this one isn't getting used enough.

The price includes the gun as shown with ergo grip, a few magpul rail covers, a magpul sling attachment, one Rock River 30rd magazine, and original Rock River plastic case.  I'm happy to swap on the original hogue grip if you prefer that.

The Vortex Razor HD scope is not included in the price, but I'm happy to throw it in for a reasonable price.  Great scope.
